Privacy Policy
Last modified: March 2025
At FLORATE LIMITED, we take the privacy of our users seriously. If
          you have any questions or concerns about our Privacy Policy, please
          don't hesitate to contact us via our
support form
.
If you would like to opt-out of data usage, please select the
"DO NOT USE MY DATA"
option. For more information about how your data may be used for
          interest-based advertising,
click here
.
Issues Related to Data Transfers to Foreign Countries:
To learn more about key considerations regarding data transfers to foreign countries and the potential risks
          of processing your personal data abroad,
click
              here
.
I. GENERAL TERMS
This is the Privacy Policy of FLORATE LIMITED ("we," "us," or
          "our"). The policy outlines our data protection practices and
          describes the types of information we may process when you use our
          mobile application, Chatbox (the “App”, “our App”). This policy
          applies to all users who access our App (“Users”).
PLEASE, REFER TO THE SECTION
“FOR U.S.
              RESIDENTS”
, IF YOU RESIDE IN AN U.S. STATE WITH COMPREHENSIVE DATA PRIVACY LAWS, INCLUDING THE
            CALIFORNIA CONSUMER PRIVACY ACT (CCPA), TEXAS DATA PRIVACY AND SECURITY ACT (TDPSA), VIRGINIA CONSUMER DATA
            PROTECTION ACT (VCDPA), THE UTAH CONSUMER PRIVACY ACT (UCPA) AND OTHERS.
The term "personal data" or "personal information" refers to any
          information that relates to an identified or identifiable natural
          person.
Personal data refers to any information that pertains to a natural
          person who can be directly or indirectly identified, particularly
          through an identification number or by one or more unique factors
          related to their physical, physiological, mental, economic, cultural
          or social status.
II. PROCESSED INFORMATION:
There are several categories of information that might be processed:
          (a) Functional data, (b) Payment Information, (c) Automatically
          Processed Data, (d) Contact information. Please refer to Section III
          to learn more details.
Children’s Data Collection
Our App is intended for users above the age defined as a “child” under applicable privacy laws. Guardians are
          responsible for ensuring minors do not submit personal data through the App without legally valid consent.
We interpret the term “child” as individuals under 16 years old, unless local regulations establish a
          different age threshold or explicit parental authorization is provided. We do not knowingly collect
          information from users who qualify as “child”.
Should any personal data from a child be identified without proper consent, we will immediately remove it from
          our systems. If you suspect we may have collected information from or about a child through the App without
          guardian approval, please contact us immediately.
III. THE PURPOSES OF PROCESSING DATA
We use your information for the following purposes:
To provide the App and its services: We use your information to
              provide the App and its services to you. This includes
              processing functional information and automatically processed
              information to ensure that you can access and use the App as
              intended.
(a) Functional data
To fulfill our contractual obligations and provide the requested
              services we require functional data. This is absolutely
              necessary to guarantee the full functionality of the App. Some data processing will only occur after
              obtaining your informed consent (as outlined below).
User Content: This includes any text or other content that you enter into the message field and send
              through the App (“Input”), as well as any text or other content generated by AI via the App (“Output”).
              You may use, share, and otherwise exploit your User Content for your own purposes, subject to your
              compliance with the rules and restrictions outlined in our Terms of Use. However, any use of User
              Content is solely at your own risk, and you assume all risks and responsibilities associated with such
              use. You are solely responsible for ensuring compliance with applicable laws when using User Content.
              Please note that we use third-party service providers such as Google (as defined below in the
Section
                V
), OpenAI, L.L.C., Anthropic Ireland, Limited and Anthropic, PBC, Hangzhou DeepSeek Artificial
              Intelligence Co., Ltd., Perplexity AI, Inc. for processing and creating AI-generated User Content. We also
              engage the
              third-party service provider Phrasly LLC for the purposes of checking whether your text has been written
              by AI within the in-app feature “AI Detector”. Additionally, if you choose to try the “GPT + Internet”
              feature, your Input will be processed by our third-party service providers, Microsoft Corporation and
              Google, in order to obtain Internet search results pertinent to your Input and update your Output
              accordingly. Please refer to
Section
                V
to learn more about OpenAI, L.L.C.'s, Hangzhou DeepSeek
              Artificial Intelligence Co., Ltd., Anthropic Ireland, Limited’s, Anthropic, PBC’s, Microsoft
              Corporation’s and Google’s, Perplexity AI, Inc. privacy policies and practices.
Please be aware that the transfer of your Input content to foreign countries when using DeepSeek models,
              as outlined in the section below regarding international data transfers, is carried out with your
              informed consent.
Contact Information: This includes your name, email address, and
              any other content you provide when contacting us via email or
              support form. We store and process this information using our
              cloud storage provider, Amazon.com, Inc. We use this information
              to respond to your inquiries, fulfill your requests, and provide
              you with requested services or communications.
Authorization data: You may create an account with the App via the following options:
via submitting your e-mail address;
via signing in with your Apple account; or
via signing in with your Google account.
In this case the following categories of data will be processed:
way of registration in the App (sign in with Google, sign in with Apple, sign in via e-mail);
email address;
data related to your Apple ID or Google account.
name and your profile picture in your Google account if you chose to add it.
Please consider that we do not access, share or otherwise use your Google user data. The sign in process
              is run through Google OAuth 2.0 protocol for further access of Google API, which allows you to sign in
              via your Google account. In case of any issues connected with the usage of the Google user data via
              Google API please approach Google directly.
For more information about the way Google shares your data using
              Google account linking as well as for Google contact details
              please refer to Section V of this Privacy Policy.
(b) Payment Information
Our e-commerce provider, Apple, is responsible for securely
              processing and charging for in-app purchases, and for handling
              your personal information in a safe and secure manner. We do not
              have access to or use your credit or debit card information as
              this is processed as part of the contract between you and Apple.
              You may access the rules and policies for in-app purchases
              directly from the app stores. You can access the relevant rules
              and policies for "in-app" purchases directly from the app
              stores.
To improve the App and personalize your experience: We use
              automatically processed information to analyze how users
              interact with the App, identify areas for improvement, and test
              new features and functionality. This helps us to continuously
              improve the App and provide a better service. We may use
              automatically processed information to personalize your
              experience within the App. For example, we may use this
              information to show you content that is tailored to your
              interests, or to suggest features or services that may be of
              interest to you.
(c) Automatically Processed Data
Log file information. When you access the App, log file
                information is automatically generated and reported.
                Additionally, this information may be provided when you
                install the App on your device. Our analytics tools
                automatically record specific log file information when you
                use the App, such as the start and stop time and date of
                usage, and how you interact with the App.
Mobile Device Data, including “device identifiers”. Device
                identifiers are small data files or similar data structures
                stored on or associated with your mobile device, which
                uniquely identify your mobile device (but not your
                personality). Device identifier enables generalized reporting
                or personalized content and ads by the third parties.Certain
                device identifiers are processed to improve the quality of
                customer support. We automatically process information about
                the device itself (type of device, type of operating system
                and its version, model and manufacturer, screen size, screen
                density, orientation, audio volume and battery, battery life,
                loading time, latency, framerate, device memory usage),
                information about the Internet connection (mobile carrier,
                network provider, network type, IP address, timestamp and
                duration of sessions, speed, browser), location-related
                information (IP address, the country code/ region/ state/ city
                associated with your SIM card or your device, language
                setting, time zone, neighboring commercial points of interest
                (eg. “coffee shop”)), other device identifiers: e.g. user
                identifiers (if they are set up by the App’s developer). In
                case you submit a support request, the device identifiers to
                be processed additionally comprise your device ID
                (identification number of your mobile device) and your user ID
                (the number assigned to the App upon its installation at your
                device). The processing of user ID and device ID enables us to
                review your support request in a more detailed manner as
                applied to your particular case. This therefore may allow us
                a) to expedite your support request (e.g. complete
                troubleshooting); and, if needed b) to approach you with a
                tailor-made solution for fixing the issue being of concern for
                you.
Cookies and similar technologies. When you use the App,
                cookies and similar technologies may be used (pixels, web
                beacons, scripts). A cookie is a text file containing small
                amounts of information which is downloaded to your device when
                you access the App. The text file is then sent back to the
                server each time you use the App. This enables us to operate
                the App more effectively. For example, we will know how many
                users access specific areas or features within our App and
                which links or ads they clicked on. We use this aggregated
                information to understand and optimize how our App is used,
                improve our marketing efforts, and provide content and
                features that are of interest to you. We may ask advertisers
                or other partners to serve ads or services to the App, which
                may use cookies or similar technologies.
Information about the applications. Name, API key (identifier
                for application), version, properties of our App can be
                reported for automated processing and analysis. Some services
                also record the list of applications and/or processes which
                are installed or run on your device.
Ad-related information. Information related to advertisements
                that you view, such as the time and date the ad is shown,
                whether you clicked on it or if it resulted in a conversion
                event, the content and type of the ad (such as text, image, or
                video), where it was displayed in the App, and your response
                to the ad, may be reported.
In-App Events. Analytics tools integrated into our App
                automatically capture and store data related to your in-App
                activities, such as completing tutorial steps, making in-app
                purchases or payments, triggering custom events, progressing
                through levels or stages, and any opt-out mechanisms used to
                limit data processing.
The data is processed via third-party automatic data processing
              technologies, such as advertising or analytics tools, to analyze
              certain information sent by your device through our App (e.g.,
              Identity For Advertisers for iOS devices/ Advertising ID or
              Android ID for Android devices), with your permission. This data
              is typically non-personal, meaning it cannot be directly linked
              to any specific individual, and we only access it in an
              aggregated form. However, some of these integrated tools (please
              see
Section V
for a list) may conduct automated processing of your personal
              data, including profiling. Profiling involves any form of
              automated processing of personal data used to evaluate certain
              personal aspects relating to you, particularly to analyze or
              predict aspects concerning your personal preferences, interests,
              behavior, location or movements (please refer to the list of
              data below). Automatic data processing technologies will start
              processing information as soon as you allow our App to track
              your activity. You may withdraw your permission at any time by
              checking the opt-out options in Section VIII below.
Please note that we do not have control over the information
              provided automatically to advertising or analytics tools, and
              therefore cannot take responsibility for the processing of such
              information. It is important to be aware that some services
              engage in personal data profiling and may obtain information
              related to your personality or device through technologies that
              are not under our responsibility. If your user ID is linked to
              your Facebook account, Facebook may use your device information
              in conjunction with categorized data that have already been
              recorded in its databases, such as your age, gender, or other
              demographic indicators. We do not supervise, control, or
              guarantee how third parties handle your personal data that may
              be collected through means other than our app. If you have any
              questions about the disclosure of your personal information,
              please direct them to the third parties involved (refer to
Section V
).
To communicate with you: We may use your contact information to
              communicate with you about the App, such as to provide you with
              updates, marketing notifications, respond to your inquiries and
              provide customer support. We may also arrange in-app surveys,
              which you are free to take part in to share your user experience
              with the App.
(d) Contact Information:
your name, your email
              address and data that you might enter and upload as a part of
              your support request or while you take part in our in-app
              surveys.
To conduct interviews about your experience with the App.
(e) Additional personal information:
name (real
              or alias), image and/or certain biographical data, speech, voice
              and/or appearances.
Please note that we only hold interviews with you and therefore
              process the respective personal data subject to your explicit
              consent.
To enforce our policies and protect our rights: We may use your
            information to enforce our policies and protect our rights,
            including investigating and preventing fraud, spam, or other
            unauthorized activity, and complying with legal obligations.
If we use your information for any other purpose not listed here, we
          will notify you and obtain your consent as required by applicable
          law.
IV. HOW LONG WE KEEP AND USE YOUR DATA
We will keep your personal information only for as long as necessary
          to provide the functional service of the App and to fulfill our
          legal obligations. If you decide that you no longer want us to use
          your information that we physically access and store, you can
          request that we delete your personal information and close your
          account.
However, some data may still be stored for a limited period of time
          (but no longer than necessary) if required by law (such as for
          taxation, accounting, or auditing purposes) or to maintain the
          safety and backup of data, prevent fraud, or other malicious acts.
V. SHARING OF DATA
When we integrate external services, we carefully select third-party
          providers who ensure the implementation of appropriate technical and
          organizational measures to protect your personal data. However, we
          cannot guarantee the security of any information transmitted to such
          third-party providers. We are not liable for any accidental loss or
          unauthorized access to your personal data due to the actions of
          third-party providers.
We do not rent or sell your personal data to third parties, but we
          may share information from tools like cookies, log files, device
          identifiers, and location data with third-party organizations that
          provide automatic data processing technologies for the App. We do
          not have control over these third parties' tracking technologies or
          their usage.
We may also share certain information, such as cookie data, with
          third-party advertising partners. This information enables
          third-party ad networks to deliver targeted ads that they believe
          will be of most interest to you.
In order to provide us with the necessary infrastructure for the
          delivery and improvement of our services, we may engage the
          following third-party service providers:
