If you want to know more about the privacy options and services of
          our App, including how to opt-out, please refer to the respective
          websites and privacy policies.
Our App may include links to third-party websites or services, or
          you may access our App from a third-party site. Please note that we
          are not responsible for the privacy practices of these third-party
          sites or services, including the information or content contained
          within them. You are solely responsible for any risk arising from
          your use of these third-party websites or resources.
Please note that certain third-party providers may engage
          sub-processors. This implies that your personal data collected by
          third-party providers can be shared with affiliates as well as other
          persons engaged thereby. If you want to learn more about the cases
          of sharing your personal data with sub-processors as well as the
          scope of your personal data shared therewith please refer to the
          respective websites and privacy policies of the third-party
          providers.
We may disclose your personal information in situations where it is
          necessary for legitimate reasons, such as public interest or in
          other unforeseen circumstances as required by law. We may also
          disclose your personal information in good faith to protect our
          rights, your safety, or the safety of others, investigate fraud, or
          respond to a government request.
Additionally, if we are involved in a merger, acquisition, or sale
          of all or a portion of our assets, we will notify you via prominent
          notice in our App of any change in ownership or usage of your
          personal information, as well as any options you may have regarding
          your personal information.
VI. INTERNATIONAL DATA TRANSFERS
We and third-party organizations that provide automatic data
          processing technologies for the App or our third-party advertising
          partners may transfer the information processed automatically across
          borders and from your jurisdiction to other countries or
          jurisdictions around the world.
Please be aware that this means we may transfer information,
          including personal information, to a country and jurisdiction that
          does not have the same data protection laws as in your jurisdiction.
          As a result, your personal information may be transferred to a third
          country, a territory, or one or more specified sectors within that
          third country, or to an international organization where data
          protection and confidentiality regulations may not provide the same
          level of protection for personal data as your jurisdiction does. When data is transferred to a country or
          jurisdiction with significantly different data protection laws than yours, we provide clear information
          about the potential risks. This enables you to make an informed decision regarding the transfer and the use
          of related features in our App. Please refer to the details below.
By using the App, you agree that we may transfer your personal data
          to any third country, a territory, or one or more specified sectors
          within that third country, or to an international organization.
For data storage purposes, we use the services of hosting providers.
          We take your privacy seriously and, where possible, encrypt your
          personal data before sending it to the hosting providers for
          storage. Please note that we only work with hosting providers that
          have passed our security and reliability checks.
When you use DeepSeek models, your Input content may be transmitted to and processed by Hangzhou DeepSeek
          Artificial Intelligence Co., Ltd., based in China. The data will be stored following DeepSeek's Privacy
          Policy
https://chat.deepseek.com/downloads/DeepSeek%20Privacy%20Policy.html
Please note that
data privacy laws in China may be significantly different
from those in your
          country or
          other regions. We encourage you to read DeepSeek's Privacy Policy carefully. If you do not agree with the
          terms or have any privacy concerns, please refrain from using DeepSeek models in our App. Below, we
summarize the key points from this policy for your awareness
(for more details, please refer
          to the full
          version of DeepSeek's Privacy Policy):
Data Usage:
DeepSeek may use your data for purposes such as improving services, serving advertisements and machine
          learning. Please note that there are no opt-out options available for these purposes. For more details,
          refer to the "How We Use Your Information" section in DeepSeek's Privacy Policy.
Data Sharing:
DeepSeek's Privacy Policy does not provide a detailed list of third-party partners with whom they share
          data. Instead, it outlines general principles regarding data sharing. Data may be also shared if required
          to comply with laws, legal processes, or requests from government authorities, including those from
          Chinese authorities. For further details, see the "How We Share Your Information" section in DeepSeek's
          Privacy Policy.
Differences in other Data Protection Standards:
The data retention requirements, security measures, and your rights may differ from the privacy standards
          in your country. Please review the relevant sections in DeepSeek's Privacy Policy to understand these
          differences.
To protect your privacy, we only send your Input content to DeepSeek, without including any personally
          identifiable information such as names or emails.
If you have any concerns, you can choose not to use features that involve transferring data to foreign
          jurisdictions or avoid submitting sensitive information in your Inputs.
VII. YOUR PRIVACY RIGHTS
Applicable data protection laws give you certain rights regarding
          your personal information. You have the following options in
          relation to your personal information that was collected (please note, that your privacy rights may vary
          depending on whether you are located):
Access to Information:
You can confirm whether we process your data and request a copy of
            it, including details about how it’s used.
Data Portability:
You are eligible to receive your data in a portable, machine-readable
            format for easy transfer to other services.
Accuracy Correction:
You may ask us to update, fix, or complete your information if you
            can’t edit it yourself via your account.
Data Deletion:
You have the right to ask to delete all or some of the personal data that is
            held about you.
Restriction of Processing:
Under certain circumstances, you may have the right to limit the ways in which your personal information is
            used. The applicability of this right depends on specific data privacy law that is applicable to you.
Complaint Submission:
You can lodge a complaint with a supervisory authority if you
            consider that the processing of personal data relating to you infringes applicable data privacy regulation.
You can exercise any of the rights described above by contacting us
          through our
contact
              form
. However, please note that we can only ensure the aforementioned
          rights with respect to the information that we physically access and
          store.
If your personal information is being processed automatically, you
          may have the right to object to such processing in certain
          circumstances. If your personal information is being processed for
          direct marketing purposes, you may ask us to stop processing your
          data for these purposes. To exercise this right, please contact the
          third-party services listed in
Section IV
of this Privacy Policy to
          learn how to object to the processing of your data. Many of them
          provide clear instructions on their privacy pages, functional API,
          or other options.
VIII. HOW TO OPT OUT
Location Data Processing
Settings > Privacy > Location Services. Choose the applicable App
          and set the “Share My Location” status to “Never”. Please refer to
          this instruction:
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT203033
.
Marketing tracking
Either choose option "Limit Ad Tracking" on your iOS device in
          Settings > Privacy > Advertising or Choose option “Allow Apps to
          Request to Track" off your iOS device in Settings > Privacy >
          Tracking. Please refer to instructions here:
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT202074
,
https://support.apple.com/en-us/HT212025
Targeted Advertising
You may limit the collection of cross-app data for interest-based ads and exercise your right to restrict
          processing using the following Targeting Opt Out Tools:
          1)
Digital Advertising Alliance
,
          2)
European Interactive Digital Advertising Alliance
            (EDAA)
,
          3)
Network Advertising Initiative
            (NAI)
.
These tools are managed by third parties, and we do not control their functionality. For more information,
          visit their official websites.
After you complete an opt-out you may still receive contextual ads
          that are based on non-personal information.
IX. SECURITY OF DATA
We take the security of your personal information seriously and have
          implemented measures to protect it from loss, misuse, and
          unauthorized access, disclosure, alteration, and destruction. We
          follow industry-standard practices to protect the personal
          information submitted to us during transmission and while in our
          possession.
To safeguard your personal information, we implement technical and
          organizational measures that align with data protection principles.
          We use encryption algorithms, including hashing where feasible, to
          secure your personal data.
However, it's important to note that no method of transmission over
          the Internet, or method of electronic storage, is 100% secure. While
          we take appropriate measures to protect your personal data, we
          cannot guarantee its absolute security. In the event of a breach of
          security that compromises your personal information, we will notify
          you promptly as required by applicable law.
If you have any questions about the security of our App, you can
          contact us through the
contact
              form
.
X. CHANGES TO THE PRIVACY POLICY
To stay current with our practices and legal obligations, we make
          regular updates to this Privacy Policy.
If we make any changes to this Privacy Policy, we will update it and
          post the revised version on this page and other relevant locations.
          We may also provide you with additional forms of notice regarding
          the changes, as appropriate in the circumstances.
XI. HOW YOU CAN CONTACT US ABOUT THIS PRIVACY POLICY
You can reach out to us with any inquiries about this Privacy Policy
          by using our
contact
              form
, or by contacting us at
privacy@florate.io
FOR U.S. RESIDENTS
Please take the time to read this Section that supplements our Privacy Policy carefully. By using the
            App, you acknowledge that you have read, understood, and agree to these terms.
This Section provides additional details to our Privacy Policy and apply to you if 1) your use of the App
          involves the processing of your personal information and 2) you reside in a U.S. state with comprehensive data
          privacy laws. These laws include, but are not limited to:
California Consumer Privacy Act (CCPA);
Texas Data Privacy and Security Act (TDPSA);
Virginia Consumer Data Protection Act (VCDPA);
Colorado Privacy Act (CPA);
Connecticut Data Privacy Act (CTDPA) and others (collectively referred to as “U.S. Privacy laws”).
To learn more about the types of data we process, the purposes of processing visit the relevant sections of
          our Privacy Policy:
Section II PROCESSED INFORMATION
>>
Section III THE PURPOSES OF PROCESSING DATA
>>
PERSONAL DATA
This Section applies only to information that identifies or can reasonably be linked to you as an individual.
          It does not cover data that has been de-identified, aggregated, or made publicly available, as such
          information is not considered "personal data" under some U.S. Privacy laws.
SHARING OF YOUR PERSONAL INFORMATION
Learn about the methods of sharing your information in
Section V
. Please be aware that all third-party processors of user
          data are service providers who use such information in accordance with a contractual agreement and for a
          business purpose. To prevent the sharing of device identifiers and geolocation data with service providers,
          please refer to your device settings for instructions on opting out, as described above in
Section VIII
.
SALE OF DATA
We do not engage in the sale of any of your personal data to third parties. While we do not sell your personal
          information for money, some U.S. Privacy laws consider sharing data for advertising purposes a “sale”. If this
          applies, you can opt out (refer to
Section VIII
).
YOUR RIGHTS
As if this Section is relevant to you you’ll be able to exercise all rights in accordance with
Section VII
. However, some aspects related
          to these rights may vary slightly from one jurisdiction/state to another, therefore, you may want to consider
          these differences when submitting your user privacy request.
Depending on your state and the relevant U.S. Privacy laws, you may also have the right to:
Opt-out of
1) the “sharing” of your personal information for “cross-contextual behavioral advertising,” often
                referred to as “interest-based advertising” or “targeted advertising;
2) the use of automated decision making in relation to your personal information;
3) any future “sales” or “sharing” of your personal information as defined by applicable U.S. Privacy
                laws.
To exercise the rights conferred on you by the U.S. Privacy laws without discrimination.
Right to Opt Out
To stop tracking your аd preferences via your device, please refer to
Section VIII “Marketing tracking”
.
Limiting access to your advertising identifier may not prevent personalized ads from all sources. Many
          companies and networks participating in industry self-regulation programs offer independent opt-out tools. To
          explore these options, visit
Section VIII “Targeted
            Advertising”
.
Certain advertising and analytics platforms provide their own tools for managing data preferences. Examples
          include
Google’s ad settings
,
"Facebook about ads" page
, and
AppsFlyer’s
opt-out feature. For a current list of our service providers (processors), see
Section V
.
Please know that opting out of interest-based advertising does not mean that you will not receive advertising.
          You may still receive ads, but those ads may be less relevant to your interests.
YOUR RIGHT TO REQUEST
If you wish to request access, portability, deletion or correction of inaccuracies (if applicable) of your
          personal information, please get in touch with us using the provided
contact form
.
When submitting a request, please take note of the following:
include in its text the phrase “Exercising my rights to maintain confidentiality in … State”, replacing
            '...' with the name of the state of your residence. We will make every effort to satisfy any request you
            make to exercise any of your privacy rights;
describe your request with enough detail for us to understand and respond to it properly;
provide sufficient information to allow us to reasonably verify your identity (your name, address, city,
            state, zip code, and email address).
We may use this information to ask you security questions to verify your identity. If you are making a request
          through an authorized agent, they must provide written authorization or a power of attorney signed by you to
          confirm their authority to act on your behalf.
In order to fulfill your request, we must be able to verify your identity and confirm that the personal
          information pertains to you. If we cannot verify your identity or the authenticity of the request, we may not
          be able to fulfill your request or respond to your request. To verify your identity, we may require additional
          information or documentation. We may also perform identity checks, including through third-party verification
          services. These measures are in place to protect the security and privacy of your personal information and
          prevent unauthorized disclosure or modification.
We will handle any personal information provided in a verifiable consumer request with care and ensure that it
          is only used for the purpose of verifying the requestor's identity or authority to make the request. We will
          maintain this information for a reasonable period required for the above-stated purpose and dispose of it
          after the purpose has been accomplished.
We aim to respond to your verifiable consumer request within 45 days of receiving it. If we need more time to
          respond, we will notify you in writing of the reason and the extension period. It is important to note that we
          are only obligated to fulfill two requests per customer per year.
To learn more about the U.S. Privacy laws in comparison please refer to
ANNEX № 1
.
UPDATES TO THIS SECTION
We make regular updates to Privacy Policy and all updates made to this Section will be considered as
          amendments to Privacy Policy. To be informed of updates, please review the latest published version of Privacy
          Policy regularly.
